Colors in CSS

1. Color Names
<p style="color: red;">This is red text</p>
<p style="background-color: yellow;">This has yellow background</p>


2. Hexadecimal Colors
<p style="color: #ff0000;">This is red (hex)</p>
<p style="background-color: #00ff00;">This is green background</p>


3. RGB Colors

<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">This is blue (RGB)</p>
<p style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);">Yellow background</p>


4. RGBA Colors (with transparency)

<p style="background-color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5);">
  Semi-transparent red background
</p>



Text in CSS

1. Text Color

p { color: blue; }


2. Text Alignment

h1 { text-align: center; }
p { text-align: justify; }




3. Text Decoration

a { text-decoration: none; }   /* removes underline */
h2 { text-decoration: underline; }



4. Text Transformation

h1 { text-transform: uppercase; }  /* ALL CAPS */
p { text-transform: capitalize; }  /* First Letter Capital */


5. Text Spacing

p {
  letter-spacing: 2px;    /* space between letters */
  word-spacing: 5px;      /* space between words */
  line-height: 1.8;       /* space between lines */
}


6. Font Style


p {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 20px;
  font-style: italic;
  font-weight: bold;
}



Final Demo Code

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Colors and Text in CSS</title>
  <style>
    h1 { color: #ff6600; text-align: center; text-transform: uppercase; }
    p { color: rgb(0, 100, 200); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.6; }
    .highlight { background-color: yellow; text-decoration: underline; }
    a { color: green; text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { color: red; text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Colors and Text in CSS</h1>
  <p>This is a normal paragraph with custom <span class="highlight">highlighted text</span>.</p>
  <p style="background-color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.2);">This paragraph has transparent background.</p>
  <a href="#">Click Me</a>
</body>
</html>







